Class ValueSet<T>

  • java.lang.Object

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the value type
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Cloneable, Iterable<T>, Collection<T>, Iterator<T>, List<T>, RandomAccess
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    FloatTuple
    public class ValueSet<T>
extends ArrayList<T>
implements Iterator<T>
    A value model which can encapsulate the values of a multi value property with an embedded iterator and a general 'getValue()' access to the current value of the iterator or to the single value. This is used in the widgets embedded in a multi widget tag to access the values in transparent way without knowledge about the multi value context.
    See Also:
    PropertyEditHandle, Serialized Form
